Similar to the above comment, this can just be cleaned up to use `wait_util` like
```
def sync_mempools(rpc_connections, *, wait=1, timeout=60, flush_scheduler=True):
    """
    Wait until everybody has the same transactions in their memory
    pools
    """
    def equal_mempool():
        mempool_sets = [set(r.getrawmempool()) for r in rpc_connections]
        return mempool_sets.count(mempool_sets[0]) == len(mempool_sets)

    wait_until(equal_mempool, timeout=timeout, wait=wait)
    if flush_scheduler:
        for r in rpc_connections:
            r.syncwithvalidationinterfacequeue()
```

I tested both changes in [this commit](https://github.com/conscott/bitcoin/commit/3001cf4d93d10831a1e891ea2b80caf74bc84816) and everything seems to pass, however let me know if you thinks its better suited for a follow up PR.

